22/07/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul travels to Washington on Tuesday (22 July) for four days of talks with US officials on improving bilateral ties and the possible deployment of Turkish peacekeepers in Iraq. "Trust with the United States has to be restored and relations have to be put on a healthy basis," Gul said. On Monday, US Ambassador to Ankara Robert Pearson said Gul's visit was part of a "serious dialogue" aimed at putting relations back on track. (Hurriyet - 22/07/03; AP, AFP, Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 21/07/03)
